		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just an opinion, but i think in-game tutorials are more elegant when they're implied, rather than stated. If the level design manages to silently guide you on your way without explicitly/openly telling you instructions, i think that's perfect. But arrows and button instructions are decidedly the more sureproof way.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
