	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've noticed several gestures for jumping down in platformers.<br /><br />Games using Down (any): <em>Kirby Super Star</em><br />Games using Down Down: <em>The Curse of Possum Hollow</em><br />Games using Down+A: <em>Chip 'n Dale's Rescue Rangers</em>, <em>Contra</em><br />Games using Down tap:* <em>Super Smash Bros. Brawl</em><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: 85%; line-height: normal">* In <em>Super Smash Bros.</em> series, &quot;tap&quot; refers to quickly moving the analog Control Stick from center to edge, or (in the case of the sideways Wii Remote in <em>Brawl</em> and <em>For</em>) quickly pressing and releasing Down on the Control Pad before the transition to crouch finishes animating.</span>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


